text: Jackie Patea-Fereti (born 30 September 1986) was a New Zealand rugby union player. She played for the New Zealand women's national rugby union team at the 2014 Women's Rugby World Cup. From 2006 to 2018, she played for Wellington Pride. == References == Category:1986 births Category:Living people Category:New Zealand rugby union players
